---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="How to Share Your Pitch Deck Without Losing Control" description="Track who views your deck, see which slides hold attention, watermark every page, and set expiry. Secure pitch deck sharing for fundraising.">
  <article class="pt-32 pb-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-xs text-text-tertiary font-mono mb-4">March 6, 2026</p>
      <h1 class="font-mono font-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl text-foreground mb-6 leading-tight">
        How to Share Your Pitch Deck Without Losing Control
      </h1>

      <div class="prose-cloak space-y-6 text-text-secondary font-sans leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          You've spent months on your pitch deck. Market analysis, traction metrics, financial
          projections, the unfair advantage slide you rewrote twelve times. Now you're sending
          it to 30 VCs.
        </p>
        <p>
          Here's what you don't know: which ones actually opened it, who forwarded it to their
          partners, and whether your financials are sitting in the inbox of a competitor's CEO.
          PDF attachments and Google Drive links give you zero visibility.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-mono font-medium text-xl text-foreground mt-10 mb-4">What investors actually do with your deck</h2>
        <p>
          Investors forward decks. It's not personal — it's how diligence works. They send it
          to partners for internal review, share it with domain experts, and sometimes forward
          it to portfolio companies building in your space. This is normal. But you should
          know it's happening.
        </p>
        <p>
          Most founders never get that visibility. They send the deck into the void and wait
          for replies that never come, wondering if the deck even landed.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-mono font-medium text-xl text-foreground mt-10 mb-4">What you need</h2>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-2 my-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent text-xs mt-1">+</span> <strong>Email verification</strong> — Know exactly who viewed your deck. Verified identity, not a guess.</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent text-xs mt-1">+</span> <strong>Per-slide analytics</strong> — Which slides held attention? Did they skip to traction or read sequentially?</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent text-xs mt-1">+</span> <strong>Watermarks</strong> — Viewer's email on every page. A deterrent against casual forwarding.</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent text-xs mt-1">+</span> <strong>Expiry</strong> — Deck expires the day your round closes. Control the window.</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent text-xs mt-1">+</span> <strong>Instant notifications</strong> — Know the moment someone opens your deck. Follow up while they're thinking about it.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="font-mono font-medium text-xl text-foreground mt-10 mb-4">How it works with CloakShare</h2>
        <p>
          Upload your deck once. Get a secure link back. Send to investors. Watch analytics in real-time.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-lg p-5 my-8">
          <pre class="text-sm font-mono text-text-secondary overflow-x-auto"><span class="text-text-tertiary">$</span> curl -X POST https://api.cloakshare.dev/v1/links \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer ck_live_xxx" \
    -F file=@pitch-deck.pdf \
    -F expires_in="30d" \
    -F watermark=true \
    -F require_email=true

<span class="text-accent">{"secure_url": "https://view.cloakshare.dev/s/lnk_aBcDeF9"}</span></pre>
        </div>
        <p>
          You send that link to an investor. They click it, enter their email (verified), and
          start reading. Every page is watermarked with their email and timestamp. Meanwhile,
          your dashboard shows:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-2 my-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent text-xs mt-1">+</span> <strong>3:15 PM:</strong> investor@sequoia.com opened the deck</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent text-xs mt-1">+</span> <strong>3:17 PM:</strong> Jumped to slide 4 (market opportunity)</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent text-xs mt-1">+</span> <strong>3:22 PM:</strong> 5 minutes on slide 6 (traction metrics)</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent text-xs mt-1">+</span> <strong>3:27 PM:</strong> Finished. Total time: 12 minutes. Completion: 95%</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="font-mono font-medium text-xl text-foreground mt-10 mb-4">Reading the signals</h2>
        <p>
          The analytics tell you everything about investor interest:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-2 my-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent text-xs mt-1">+</span> <strong>5 min on traction, skipped financials:</strong> They like the market. Lead with unit economics next call.</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent text-xs mt-1">+</span> <strong>30 seconds total, 2 pages:</strong> Not interested. Don't follow up. Move on.</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent text-xs mt-1">+</span> <strong>Opened twice, weeks apart:</strong> They're reconsidering. Good time for a warm follow-up.</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent text-xs mt-1">+</span> <strong>New email from a different domain opened it:</strong> They forwarded internally. It's in partner review.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Every founder fundraising has gut instinct. CloakShare turns that instinct into data.
          Stop wasting time on lukewarm leads and focus on the investors who actually engaged.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-mono font-medium text-xl text-foreground mt-10 mb-4">Free tier covers a seed round</h2>
        <p>
          Most founders send their deck to 20-50 investors. CloakShare's free tier gives you
          50 links and 500 views per month. Send 40 decks, get 3-4 opens each — you're at
          120-160 views. Comfortably in free territory.
        </p>
        <p>
          There's also a self-hosted option. Clone the repo, run
          <code class="text-accent font-mono text-sm">docker compose up</code>, and you have
          unlimited decks and views on your own server. Useful if you're running a fund or
          managing a deal room.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-mono font-medium text-xl text-foreground mt-10 mb-4">Try it</h2>
        <p>
          Sign up free at <a href="https://cloakshare.dev" class="text-accent hover:underline">cloakshare.dev</a>.
          Upload a deck, get a secure link, send it to your first investor today. You'll never
          go back to emailing PDFs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
